@database History
@master History.guide

@node "MAIN" "mathX History"

                                   @{b}History@{ub}


@{b}V1.32@{ub}        * Updated polish catalog (Lukasz Jodlowski)
(1998-11-20) * NewIcons for mathX (Luca Longone)
             * Removed french translation - it needs to be updated.
             * Fixed little bug concerning program settings
             * Fixed illegal memory access in parser.

             * Please note: There are no more keyfiles now. They are
               replaced by registration numbers. You may choose if you
               want to get your number by mail or by email. I will not
               send discs anymore. Existing keyfiles stay valid.


@{b}V1.31beta@{ub}    * 3D graph: - fixed bad bug after iconifying and
(1998-06-14)               some little drawing bugs
                         - x- and y-axis
                         - 'Test' button in settings window
                         - Show angles when rotating with mouse.
                           Cursor keys rotate, too.
                         - center graph in window
                         - another colorscheme
             * Some improvements in gfx memory allocation.
             * 68000 version again.
             * Again restructured math kernel. It should be faster
               and use less memory now.
             * AIRI Regsite in Poland. Discount for polish users!
             * Redesigned registration window. Feel free to use it :-)
             * Updated czech translation
             * Improved zero search a bit
             * Missing simplification in "A*x=B"
             * Fixed MathScript export


@{b}V1.30@{ub}        * Polish catalog and some new example functions by
(1998-05-07)   Lukasz Jodlowski.
             * Exponential numbers, e.g. 1.23e-5
             * Fixed term display bug (thanks to Luca Longone)
             * 3D graph: - colorized plots
                         - wire frame mouse manipulation instead of
                           sliders
             * 2D graph: - fixed some bugs (autorange, zoom, log)
                         - numbers stay visible if axis is on the
                           left or bottom
                         - trace a function in the coordinate-mouse-mode
                           by clicking on the function and moving mouse
                         - data plots from matrices
             * Data table input window for data plots.
             * 68020 version only. Mail me if you still need 68000!
             * Fixed 'Remove' button bug in 2D graph settings.
             * Only one (english) History.guide for all languages, no
               need to translate it.
             * Fixed function of help key in many windows


@{b}V1.21beta@{ub}    * New matrix tools window with a nice matrix input field
(1998-04-03)   and some new matrix operations. It replaces the three
               old matrix windows.
             * New '>' and '<' operators.
               Removed 'rang' because it did not work well.
             * Fixed bug in parser that froze mathX after entering
               an incorrect term with the ":=" operator.
             * Definitions got lost under certain circumstances. This
               caused for example a flat 3D graph when drawing one
               of the form() demo-functions.
             * Intern: made two minimal changes in Term display for
               debugging.


@{b}V1.20beta@{ub}    * Redesigned 2D graph and 2D graph settings window.
(1998-03-03) * Wrong simplification of sqrt(x^<even number>),
               fixed missing parentheses when simplifying "a/(b+c)".
             * Updated translations: french, czech.
             * Reworked install script.
             * Fixed some MUI background problems. User interface images
               do not disappear anymore because it just didn't work well
               in MUI.
             * Fixed bug in term display window.
             * Major internal cleanups, fixed small memory leaks.
             * This beta version is much slower in symbolic calculations
               than the old versions, because I had to disable my own
               fast-but-buggy memory management.


@{b}V1.11@{ub}        * French catalog updated.
(97-02-09)   * Fixed ln().
             * Fixed bug in 2D graph printing that was introduced by V1.10b
             * Better user notification of internal errors. This should
               help to find out why mathX fails - if it fails.
             * The windows are snapshotable again.
             * "Cut" gadget stayed ghosted after entering term without
               "new".
             * Some internal cleanups (KaiLib).


@{b}V1.10b@{ub}       * Italian catalog thanks to M.Berionne and M.Giorato
(97-01-20)   * Fixed crash when closing a running discussion window.
               Blocking status window now.
             * Status window in determinant, too.
             * ln() can be used instead of log().
             * Fixed delay after entering very very large numbers.
             * Save as IFF now with compression.
             * Fixed those strange vertical lines in SIRDS graph.
             * Reduced nerving frequency!
             * 2D graph: - Bigger mouse cross
                         - fixed bold rasterlines,
                         - fixed wrong label and key shortcuts in settings
             * Intern  : - Cleaned up MathScript export.
                         - Cleaned (and speed) up dimension calculation of
                           term display.
                         - Extra class for Oper1.
                         - No more ugly memory fragmentation when creating
                           plain text out of symbol nodes.
                         - Introduced system independent graphic interface


@{b}V1.02@{ub}        * Fixed fatal crash when (de)iconifying 2D-graph
(96-12-20)   * Context menus in all graph windows and term display window
             * Parser improvements: Parser accepts spaces like "1 + 2*x",
               handles implicit multiplication like "(1+x)(1+2x)" or "5x"
               and allows to leave out the function brackets, so you can
               write "sin x" instead of "sin(x)"


@{b}V1.01@{ub}        * Derivative of tan(x) was wrong
(96-12-06)   * Fixed key shortcuts for some term gadgets
             * Fixed exponential number output (e.g. in 2D graph zooming),
               that could not be interpreted
             * Fixed crash in 3D saving. I know that printing and saving
               in mathX is still not satisfying in some other aspects ;-)
             * 'Delete functions' button in 2D-graph
             * Image button switch in 3D-graph should work now
             * intern: version strings out of catalogs, recompiled with
                       MCPP4 - it's not that bad ;-)


@{b}V1.00@{ub}        This is the first public version of mathX. It has been written to
(96-11-10)   replace my old program Graph2D. The keyfiles of the
             registered users of Graph2D can be used for mathX, too: Just
             move the "Graph2D.key" from your Graph2D drawer to your mathX
             drawer and rename it to "mathX.key".

             mathX is a completely new written program, so there is no
             exact list of changes between Graph2D and mathX. mathX looks
             similar to Graph2D, so I hope that Graph2D users won't have
             difficulties in using mathX now. Please read documentation
             anyway!

             So what are the most important news?

             * mathX uses rational numbers instead of floating point
               numbers. This will give maximum precision in all symbolic
               operations like derivation, evaluation, etc. Despite that
               the speed of numerical operations like discussion, graph
               drawing, etc. has been increased significantly.

             * Heavily improved simplifications.

             * Support of matrices and vectors. There is a new LinAlg menu
               featuring calculation of determinante and inverse, solving
               of linear systems, characteristical polynom.

             * 2D graph has new features and settings: logarithmical
               display, optional autorange, color and linestyle selectable
               for everything, ...
               You can define a range and step for an optional 2nd argument
               of a function.

             * Functions - they're called expressions now - can be dragged'
               n'dropped from or to every window. Furthermore you do not
               have to give give a name to every stupid function: just
               enter for example "3*x^2-x+2" and let it draw, discuss it, ...

             * All text fields are able to handle mathematical expressions
               if they make sense: for example in the 2D graph settings
               field "x axis from" you can enter an expression like "-2*pi".

             * Bubble help is available for all GUI elements. Just don't
               move your mouse pointer for some seconds and you will see
               short help texts.

             * SIRDS graph algorithm has been rewritten to run much faster.
               Take a look at it! There was also a little error in the 3D
               effect that has been fixed.

             * Term display looks better now thanks to a size sensitive
               line thickness and smaller exponents.
@endnode
